about: As British Columbia’s largest inland port, Ashcroft Terminal is strategically located to help shippers, manufacturers and producers prepare their commodities for export or import. Located at the Eastern end of CP/CN mainline co-production, Ashcroft is the last location westbound, and the first location eastbound, at which mainline traffic can stop, to or from, Metro Vancouver. Every railcar that travels on the Class 1 mainlines, must go directly through Ashcroft Terminal. Steadily expanding infrastructure since 2007, Ashcroft Terminal now maintains 60,000ft of internal track, 730+ rail car spots, and 40,000 sq.ft. of warehouse space on 320 acres. The Terminal serves 7,000 railcars and 6,000 trucks annually while providing a variety of value-add services to its diverse customer base.

about: MacMillan-Piper is a trusted leader in transloading, warehousing, and logistics, serving businesses nationwide. With over 50 years of expertise, we specialize in handling diverse cargo—lumber, paper, steel, refrigerated goods, and more—through our strategically located facilities near the Ports of Seattle and Tacoma. Our mission is to provide cost-effective, reliable, and seamless logistics solutions, allowing clients to focus on their core operations. As a U.S. Customs Freight Station (CFS) and USDA-certified facility, we streamline imports and exports while ensuring compliance. Our heavy lift and oversized transloading operations has enhanced our service offering to meet the unique needs of our clients and our partnership with GSC has satisfied the need to support end to end solutions to our clients. Committed to innovation, integrity, and client satisfaction, we continuously develop tailored solutions that enhance supply chain efficiency. Whether by rail, truck, or container, MacMillan-Piper delivers trusted logistics solutions to keep businesses moving forward.

about: Front Range Transload is a multi-commodity transload facility locally owned and operated in Pueblo, Colorado. We are conveniently located with direct access to major North/South and East/West interstates to allow for convenient access to all the Southwest United States. Front Range Transload is the only BNSF Premier Transload Facility in Southern Colorado. FRT strives to develop and implement invaluable partner relationships with a focus on new and innovative transload solutions. We offer all-in-one transload services, including in-house trucking, delivery, and short and long-term storage. Our all-inclusive model allows us to be the most cost effective and reliable option for moving freight in Southern Colorado.

about: Afar Logistics, LLC is a full-service logistics company specializing in warehouse and transloading services, ocean container yard storage, own chassis leasing, and regional and local drayage. With a focus on efficiency and cost-effectiveness, Afar Logistics provides storage solutions for various products and materials, handling multiple container sizes and types. The company offers a fleet chassis for our customers use and can accommodate live loading and unloading, leaving containers and chassis overnight for customers’ convenience. Afar Logistics has a fleet of tractors and equipment supplied by independent contractors. At Afar Logistics, this enables the company to offer container drayage to and from various ports in the Seattle, Tacoma, and Portland areas at reasonable rates. The company boasts a spotless safety record and strives to maintain a 100% on-time delivery and pickup rate.

Environmental Remediation and Recovery, Inc. (ER&R) is a
railcar cleaning and transloading facility strategically located off the North / South Canadian National (CN) mainline Mounds, Illinois (Southern Illinois). about: A&G Transport Inc. operates a 42,000 sq ft warehouse facility in Oakland, CA, just minutes from the Port of Oakland. Our facility is equipped to handle high-volume freight with services including transloading, cross-docking, restacking, palletizing, and block-and-brace solutions. With a fleet of over 55 trucks and more than a decade of logistics experience, we provide drayage services from the port to our warehouse and final delivery to cities across California and Nevada. about: TheOklahoma Central Rail Park (OKCRP)is a200-acre rail-served industrial and logistics facilitylocated inEl Reno, Oklahoma, just west of Oklahoma City and less than two miles fromInterstate 40. It is operated under agreement byJaguar Transport Holdingsand offers customers rail access via a connection with theUnion Pacific Railroad. The park is equipped withunit train capacity, transload tracks, truck scales, multiple silos, and extensive outdoor laydown and developable acreage, allowing it to handle a wide variety of commodities including agricultural products, petroleum, lumber, aggregate, and other bulk goods. OKCRP provides a flexible solution for shippers that need efficient rail service without having their own rail-served facilities, and its strategic location supports access to regional markets around Oklahoma City.

about: TheMissouri Eastern Railroad (reporting mark MER)is aClass III short-line freight railroadinMissourithat began operations onMarch 1, 2022as a subsidiary ofJaguar Transport Holdings. It operates roughly53–60 milesof formerChicago, Rock Island and Pacific Railroadline in theSt. Louis metropolitan area, running from nearUnionthroughVigustoOverland, where it interchanges with theTerminal Railroad Association of St. Louis. MER’s trackage includes rights over Union Pacific-owned sections and combines purchased and leased segments of the historic route. The railroad serves a diversified group of customers—such as producers of plastics, paper products, fly ash, building materials, and food products—and offers car storage, repair, and transload services. Its strategic location near multiple Class I connections, major highways, and the Mississippi River provides significant freight access for shippers and supports regional commercial and industrial development

about: TheSouthwestern Railroad (reporting mark SW)is aClass III short-line freight railroadbased inDeming, New Mexico, that has operated since1990over formerAtchison, Topeka & Santa Fe Railway (Santa Fe)trackage in southwestern New Mexico. It serves communities such asDeming, Whitewater, Tyrone, and Chino, hauling key commodities includingcopper and related materials, limestone, and chemicals, largely tied to local mining and industrial customers. The railroad interchanges withBNSF Railway and Union Pacificand provides freight service, railcar storage, and support to regional shippers. Originally consisting of multiple disconnected divisions, the Southwestern Railroad’s primary remaining operation is itsWhitewater Divisionin New Mexico. InNovember 2020, the line was acquired byJaguar Transport Holdings, which continues to operate and develop the railroad within its network of short lines.

about: TheCimarron Valley Railroad (reporting mark CVR)is aClass III short-line freight railroadoperating about254 miles of trackthrough parts ofKansas, Oklahoma, and Colorado, headquartered inSatanta, Kansas. It was formed in1996when it acquired former Atchison, Topeka and Santa Fe Railway lines and runs southwest fromDodge City, Kansas, to Satanta, where the route splits with one branch continuing toBoise City, Oklahoma, and another toSpringfield, Colorado. The railroad primarily haulsagricultural commoditiessuch as wheat, corn, milo, and related products, along with fertilizer, chemicals, sand, and other goods, serving rural shippers and interchanging withBNSF Railwayat Dodge City. Over the years it has received state and federal grants for locomotive and infrastructure upgrades to enhance service and efficiency. In2020, CVR was purchased byJaguar Transport Holdings, reflecting continued investment in the line’s operations and regional freight capacity.

about: As British Columbia’s largest inland port, Ashcroft Terminal is strategically located to help shippers, manufacturers and producers prepare their commodities for export or import. Located at the Eastern end of CP/CN mainline co-production, Ashcroft is the last location westbound, and the first location eastbound, at which mainline traffic can stop, to or from, Metro Vancouver. Every railcar that travels on the Class 1 mainlines, must go directly through Ashcroft Terminal. Steadily expanding infrastructure since 2007, Ashcroft Terminal now maintains 60,000ft of internal track, 730+ rail car spots, and 40,000 sq.ft. of warehouse space on 320 acres. The Terminal serves 7,000 railcars and 6,000 trucks annually while providing a variety of value-add services to its diverse customer base.

about: MacMillan-Piper is a trusted leader in transloading, warehousing, and logistics, serving businesses nationwide. With over 50 years of expertise, we specialize in handling diverse cargo—lumber, paper, steel, refrigerated goods, and more—through our strategically located facilities near the Ports of Seattle and Tacoma. Our mission is to provide cost-effective, reliable, and seamless logistics solutions, allowing clients to focus on their core operations. As a U.S. Customs Freight Station (CFS) and USDA-certified facility, we streamline imports and exports while ensuring compliance. Our heavy lift and oversized transloading operations has enhanced our service offering to meet the unique needs of our clients and our partnership with GSC has satisfied the need to support end to end solutions to our clients. Committed to innovation, integrity, and client satisfaction, we continuously develop tailored solutions that enhance supply chain efficiency. Whether by rail, truck, or container, MacMillan-Piper delivers trusted logistics solutions to keep businesses moving forward.

about: Front Range Transload is a multi-commodity transload facility locally owned and operated in Pueblo, Colorado. We are conveniently located with direct access to major North/South and East/West interstates to allow for convenient access to all the Southwest United States. Front Range Transload is the only BNSF Premier Transload Facility in Southern Colorado. FRT strives to develop and implement invaluable partner relationships with a focus on new and innovative transload solutions. We offer all-in-one transload services, including in-house trucking, delivery, and short and long-term storage. Our all-inclusive model allows us to be the most cost effective and reliable option for moving freight in Southern Colorado.

about: Afar Logistics, LLC is a full-service logistics company specializing in warehouse and transloading services, ocean container yard storage, own chassis leasing, and regional and local drayage. With a focus on efficiency and cost-effectiveness, Afar Logistics provides storage solutions for various products and materials, handling multiple container sizes and types. The company offers a fleet chassis for our customers use and can accommodate live loading and unloading, leaving containers and chassis overnight for customers’ convenience. Afar Logistics has a fleet of tractors and equipment supplied by independent contractors. At Afar Logistics, this enables the company to offer container drayage to and from various ports in the Seattle, Tacoma, and Portland areas at reasonable rates. The company boasts a spotless safety record and strives to maintain a 100% on-time delivery and pickup rate.

about: TheOklahoma Central Rail Park (OKCRP)is a200-acre rail-served industrial and logistics facilitylocated inEl Reno, Oklahoma, just west of Oklahoma City and less than two miles fromInterstate 40. It is operated under agreement byJaguar Transport Holdingsand offers customers rail access via a connection with theUnion Pacific Railroad. The park is equipped withunit train capacity, transload tracks, truck scales, multiple silos, and extensive outdoor laydown and developable acreage, allowing it to handle a wide variety of commodities including agricultural products, petroleum, lumber, aggregate, and other bulk goods. OKCRP provides a flexible solution for shippers that need efficient rail service without having their own rail-served facilities, and its strategic location supports access to regional markets around Oklahoma City.

about: TheMissouri Eastern Railroad (reporting mark MER)is aClass III short-line freight railroadinMissourithat began operations onMarch 1, 2022as a subsidiary ofJaguar Transport Holdings. It operates roughly53–60 milesof formerChicago, Rock Island and Pacific Railroadline in theSt. Louis metropolitan area, running from nearUnionthroughVigustoOverland, where it interchanges with theTerminal Railroad Association of St. Louis. MER’s trackage includes rights over Union Pacific-owned sections and combines purchased and leased segments of the historic route. The railroad serves a diversified group of customers—such as producers of plastics, paper products, fly ash, building materials, and food products—and offers car storage, repair, and transload services. Its strategic location near multiple Class I connections, major highways, and the Mississippi River provides significant freight access for shippers and supports regional commercial and industrial development

about: TheOregon Eastern Railroad (reporting mark OERR)is ashort-line freight railroadbased inVale, Oregon, operating on about24–27 miles of trackbetweenOntario and Vale/Celatomin eastern Oregon. It connects with theUnion Pacific Railroadat Ontario and serves local industries—includingEP Minerals, agricultural suppliers, propane, and urea shippers—while also offering railcar storage and transload services. Originally part of a Union Pacific branch and later operated by the Wyoming Colorado Railroad, the line was acquired in2020 by Jaguar Transport Holdingsand continues to provide “last-mile” freight service that links regional customers to the national rail network.

about: TheSouthwestern Railroad (reporting mark SW)is aClass III short-line freight railroadbased inDeming, New Mexico, that has operated since1990over formerAtchison, Topeka & Santa Fe Railway (Santa Fe)trackage in southwestern New Mexico. It serves communities such asDeming, Whitewater, Tyrone, and Chino, hauling key commodities includingcopper and related materials, limestone, and chemicals, largely tied to local mining and industrial customers. The railroad interchanges withBNSF Railway and Union Pacificand provides freight service, railcar storage, and support to regional shippers. Originally consisting of multiple disconnected divisions, the Southwestern Railroad’s primary remaining operation is itsWhitewater Divisionin New Mexico. InNovember 2020, the line was acquired byJaguar Transport Holdings, which continues to operate and develop the railroad within its network of short lines.

about: TheCimarron Valley Railroad (reporting mark CVR)is aClass III short-line freight railroadoperating about254 miles of trackthrough parts ofKansas, Oklahoma, and Colorado, headquartered inSatanta, Kansas. It was formed in1996when it acquired former Atchison, Topeka and Santa Fe Railway lines and runs southwest fromDodge City, Kansas, to Satanta, where the route splits with one branch continuing toBoise City, Oklahoma, and another toSpringfield, Colorado. The railroad primarily haulsagricultural commoditiessuch as wheat, corn, milo, and related products, along with fertilizer, chemicals, sand, and other goods, serving rural shippers and interchanging withBNSF Railwayat Dodge City. Over the years it has received state and federal grants for locomotive and infrastructure upgrades to enhance service and efficiency. In2020, CVR was purchased byJaguar Transport Holdings, reflecting continued investment in the line’s operations and regional freight capacity.

about: TheTexas & Eastern Railroad (reporting mark?TERR)is ashort-line freight railroadoperating ineastern Texas, primarily betweenPalestine and Rusk, Texas, on about30 miles of trackleased from theTexas State Railroad Authority.It connects with theUnion Pacific RailroadatPalestineand servesAnderson and Cherokee counties, hauling commodities such asconstruction aggregates, industrial products, and chemicals, and offering services likerailcar storageand transloading. Originally part of the historicTexas State Railroadfreight line founded in1881, it now functions as a modern common-carrier freight route underJaguar Transport Holdings’operation while the associated heritage tourist trains continue under the Texas State Railroad name.
